    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="Gwoza LGA had the greatest proportion of households categorized with “high” or “very high” needs (39%), compared to other East Borno LGAs, due in large part to unmet shelter/NFI (84%), livelihoods (71%), food security (63%), protection (38%), WASH (16%), and nutrition (15%) needs. Much of these needs are due to recent influxes of IDPs and returnees to Gwoza and Pulka towns since the beginning of 2018, making it difficult for humanitarian actors to keep up with meeting basic needs . More than half of households reported insecurity as a barrier to accessing agricultural land (57%), highlighting how insecurity in the area is contributing to poor livelihoods."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 47 60 73 86 99 112 125 138 151 164 177 190 203 216 229 242 255 268 281 294 307 320 333 346 359 372 385 398 411 424 437 450 463 476 489 502 515 528 541 554 567 580 593 606 619 632 645 658 671 684 697 710 723 736 749 762 775 788 801 814 827 840 853 866 879 892 905 918 931 944 957 970 983 996 1009 1022 1035 1048 1061 1074 1087 1100 1113 1126 1139 1152 1165 1178 1191 1204 1217 1230 1243 1256 1269 1282 1295 1308 1321 1334 1347 1360 1373 1386 1399 1412 1425 1438 1451 1464 1477 1490 1503 1516 1529 1542 1555 1568 1581 1594 1607 1620 1633 1646 1659 1672 1685 1698 1711 1724 1737 1750 1763 1776 1789 1802 1815 1828 1876 1841 1888 1846 1900 1851 1912 1856 1924 1861 1936 1866 1941 1871 1953 1958 1970 1975 1994 1999 1881 1893 1905 1917 1929 2018 1946 1963 1980 1987 2011 2004 2032 2025 2035 2028 2039 2052"/>
